friends and he had his but - if they were going out such as the weekends, if they were going anywhere and taking us children with them well the - both the friends - pair of friends used to - go like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid221165 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 Would these people who were counted as friends be allowed to come into your house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14048569 AN  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 No. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid221165 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 So no one called casually without an invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14048569 AN  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 No. No, they wouldn't have 'em in, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid221165 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 But they would go out to visit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14048569 AN  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid221165 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 People often tell us that in those days they 
made their own amusements, what do you think your grandparents did when they got together with their friends or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14048569 AN  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 Well I think that they must have had a sing-song, something like that. They always used to seem pleasant. They were a pleasant
 pair and - they could really make their own amusement at home you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid221165 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 
Many people divide society into different social classes or groups, in that time before 1918 did you think of some people belonging to one class and some to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14048569 AN  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 Well yes, we used to think some people weren't as good as we were and - that, you know, the poorer people we didn't just -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid221165 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 So you were aware that there were sort of divisions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14048569 AN  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid221165 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 What class would you have put yourself in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14048569 AN  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 Well I should have said we were middle class of a sort really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid221165 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 What sort of people belonged to the middle class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14048569 AN  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 
Well - grandma used to mix with shopkeepers, people like a that - she wouldn't mix with the poor - well granddad wouldn't either, mix with the poorer people. You know, those that hadn't got anything to put on kind of thing.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid221165 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 What sort of people belonged to the poorer classes do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14048569 AN  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 Well - we'll say, the chap that had got clogs on and - pigeon flying and all the rest of it, he wouldn't
 let us neither play with the children nor nothing else. You see because granddad was top hat and tails, when he wasn't - oh yes, when he wasn't whatsit. Top hat and kid gloves. Oh yes, he was quite a dandy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid221165 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 Were you aware that there were people who had even more money and were above the middle class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14048569 AN  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 
Oh yes, there was people that had more money. Such as those up at the top end of Dresden and - Cartwright and Edwards's - you know, the pot man that is now. Well the Cartwrights lived up there and t
he Edwards's lived up there and Towns - Mr Twosn's boss, he lived up there. There was Sir James Kent used to live up there, not the one that is now but the - old gentleman used to live up there Dresden. Those were the rich people. They were mansions as we
 used to call them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid221165 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 Can you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort differently from people of another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14048569 AN  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 Well only as far as - the poorer class were. Those that went about in clogs and all the rest of it, we weren't allowed to speak 
to their children, not when granddad or grandma were anywhere about. If we made friends with - don't make friends with them away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid221165 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 Were you ever told to curtsey or touch your cap or show respect to anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14048569 AN  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 No. We were stopped from using - we must
n't use impudence to anyone. Well we mustn't answer anyone back, but - we weren't taught to curtsey or nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid221165 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 Was there anyone you called sir or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14048569 AN  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 Only - well they was termed - lived up what}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11608852\charrsid7613621 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11608852\charrsid7613621  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 it - up - Dresden - she was named Morran, we 
used to call her madam but - she was - well how - if I must tell you the truth I think she was on the streets.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid221165 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 In the district where you lived then big factory owners were looked upon as the most important people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14048569 AN  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid221165 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 Did you come into any contact with them?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14048569 AN  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 Wel}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11608852\charrsid7613621 l - yes, when I went to St Domin}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 ic}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11608852\charrsid7613621 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 
s High School I used to go to school with both Mr Peter Towns and - I used to go to school with Mr Brain.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid221165 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 And these people were considered important because they were wealthy and they were employing people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14048569 AN  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid221165 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 You say your gran and granddad would have been associating with shopkeepers, where would you have put clergymen and teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14048569 AN  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 Well - granddad couldn't have any clergymen in the house, only just the Catholic pr}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11608852\charrsid7613621 ie}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 st. And - of course the Catholic teachers used to come to visit you know. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid221165 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 But you saw them on the same level as your gran and granddad?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14048569 AN  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid221165 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 They weren't specially important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14048569 AN  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid221165 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 What sort of people would you say went to church and what went to chapel, in your case everybody went to the Catholic church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14048569 AN  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid221165 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 Factory owners down to the poorer classes who just happened to be Catholics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14048569 AN  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid221165 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 Where you lived did all people have the same standard of living?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14048569 AN  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid221165 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 You were conscious that there were different groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14048569 AN  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 Yes. The houses one side of the road were bigger than the others, some of them the other side were old - small little cottages, upstair}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11608852\charrsid7613621 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621  - one upstairs and one down and the ch
ildren slept where they could kind of affair. Well those were the kind that grandma wouldn't let us mix with, although I don't see why she shouldn't 'cos I aren't class conscious, I never have been.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid221165 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 So she felt she was superior in fact to them?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14048569 AN  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid221165 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 Did your gran and granddad share the same attitude about social class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14048569 AN  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid221165 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 Your gran would have described herself as being middle class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14048569 AN  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid221165 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 She would attribute this to having a bit more money than other people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14048569 AN  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid221165 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 Would you say at this time that it was possible to move from one class to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14048569 AN  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 
No, I don't think it was possible. We all seemed to be in a rut, that kind of thing you know. They didn't - I don't think it was - they could have moved f
rom one class to another because as I say they all seemed to be in a rut, they're all - what they started as - finished as.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid221165 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 Can you remember anyone being described as a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14048569 AN  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 I think that they used to say Peter Towns's father was a real gentleman but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid221165 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 Why would that be - because he treated people kindly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14048569 AN  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 Oh yes. Then the Duke of Sutherland you know, he used to come round to the houses, because he was our landlord.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid221165 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 He would be a real gentleman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14048569 AN  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 Oh ye
s, he was. Although he - as far as I can remember him he was more like a big old farmer. He was - he always used to give - we children he - it didn't matter whether we were poor or rich - used to give them something - we always used to have something off 
him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid221165 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 Do you remember seeing a policeman around where you lived as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14048569 AN  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 Oh yes, there were always policemen. There was always somebody getting locked up. Either for drunkenness or something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid221165 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 What did you think of him, did your gran ever threaten you with the police?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14048569 AN  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 Well - he once hit a police}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11608852\charrsid7613621 man with his cape because - it wa}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 s me again, I'd been climbing and - and - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11608852\charrsid7613621 he fetched me down from the wais}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 
t and he hit me with his cape and me granddad took his cape off him and hit him. He got three month for it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid221165 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 Your granddad went to prison }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11608852\charrsid7613621 for}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621  three months?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14048569 AN  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 Yes. For hitting a policeman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid221165 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 And it was all your fault really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14048569 AN  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 Yes, it was all my fault. I was a very naughty girl as a - child.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid221165 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 Apart from this how do you think the police treated the people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14048569 AN  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 
Well I think that they treated them fair generally. I remember once a fellow'd been picked up in - Comarty Street in Dresden and the policeman took him home, he was drunk, instead of locking him up, 'cos they had jus
t to lock them up you know. He took - he took him home. And I remember another time a boy stealing some - no he didn't, he shoved a - a marble up some pigeons behind and the policeman give him a good hiding instead of locking him up. I ay the police were 
very fair.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid221165 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 Your house was rented from the Duke of Sutherland?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14048569 AN  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid221165 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 Would you say he was a good landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14048569 AN  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 Yes, he was a very good landlord. He'd do - even the poorest of the poor he'd do their houses when they made complaints to him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid221165 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 Do you remember feeling that your grandparents had to struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14048569 AN  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 No. I don't think they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid221165 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 Was your granddad ever out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14048569 AN  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid221165 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 Was he ever off ill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14048569 AN  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 Not as I know of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid221165 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 So you never had to go to the Guardians or to the parish or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14048569 AN  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 Oh no. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid221165 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 When there was someone in the district who the people disapproved of very strongly what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14048569 AN  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 Well there was no one in the district that anybody disapproved of. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid221165 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 Were you given lessons by your grandparents, a tutor or a governess?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14048569 AN  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 Used to go to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid221165 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 How old were you when you first went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14048569 AN  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 I went to school - I should be - about eight and a half when I went to school here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid221165 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 Had you been to school in Ireland?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14048569 AN  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 No. I hadn't been to school. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid221165 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 Didn't people have to go in school in Ireland then at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14048569 AN  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 Well they were supposed to do but still - we were down the I.R.A. company - country and of course it - they please - they kind 
of please themselves. There's a quarrel if they come after us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid221165 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 When you started here at eight and a half you'd be going to school for the full day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14048569 AN  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid221165 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2973543\charrsid7613621 This was St Do}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11608852\charrsid7613621 m}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
